|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/12/196234           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

greenbird writes "Another patent fiasco has begun. Wired reports that a
[0]patent on location-based Internet searches was filed in 1996 and
granted in 1999 ([1]patent is here). A patent troll company name Geomas
acquired the patent and has filed suit against Verizon in none other than
[2]Marshall, Texas. They claim this is the first in what will be a long
line of lawsuits. Geomas has amassed a $20M war chest in venture capital
to use for getting rich off of a clearly obvious idea."

